<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-09T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-09T02:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1379: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-09T02:00:00-05:00">January 9, 1939—2 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 9:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 1, January 7, 3 p.m., I
                                have sent messages to other members of the Commission asking their
                                agreement to announcement of an approximate date for projected
                                visits to Managua and to Tegucigalpa. The Costa Rican member of the
                                Commission is now in Chile and possibly may visit Buenos Aires on
                                invitation of Argentine Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>